tip.text: Sip a whisky and take it slow while your barber makes you look like a demigod of handsome. This is in the top 10 best barbers I've ever been to, for experience and for cut.
I have an unfair bias against chain-type cafes... but every Coffee Company I've been to is pretty good. Good design, good coffee, good workspace. It's a better than average place to grab a coffee.

Holy shit this place is great. Came in thinking to buy weed & hit a cafe. Wound up running into Axl, High Society regular, with his strong, pothead, curious dog Diva. Stayed chatting & smoking for 1h.
Solid spot for some urban parkour. Behind it is a parking lot with a cross fit gym, some storage containers to climb, a thin ledge to walk, and a patterned 1.5 - story wall to scale.
This cozy cafe/restaurant is full of cute handmade knick-knacks. The croissant is the most delicious I've had in quite a while. Got one fresh from the oven. Oh + the beach is right across the street.
This hostels begun to feel like a second home. The family of staff and regulars is chill and eclectic and everyone's got at least two good stories.
This was an unexpectedly excellent place to do some work. The coffee is yummy and well made, the seats are comfy with enough plugs, the staff are relaxed and cool.
It's an alright cafe, but nothing special. Hard tile floor, average food and coffee, okay wifi, one plug. Just an average okay cafe.
This place is gorgeously designed to be half coworking space & half cafe/wine bar. The 80.1% Dark Hot Chocolate is delectable.
Takeout-or-delivery-only spot. Open 24/7 and has plugs tho... so if you're in a bind you can ask them to let you inside to charge. Super chill guys run the place while singing songs and smoking weed.
Welcome to the Waag. An old music hall (I think) turned restaurant. Wifi is a bit spotty, and food is average. But the interior design? Gorgeous.
Absolutely excellent cafe for getting some work done. Minimalist design, good snacks and coffee, fast wifi, and they accept Bitcoin. Awesome.
Insanely wonderful place. From the architecture around it to the exhibits inside.
Insanely delicious sashimi. The other food on the menu is average or better, but the sashimi is perfect. Their house beer is delectable, light, & fruity. Very relaxed and authentic interior design.
The sashimi bowls are absolutely delicious, and not too expensive. Highly recommended.

venue.name: Future World: Where Art Meets Science

tip.text: The decor is excellent. Manly & irreverently classy. The haircuts are better than average (though I'd say The Panic Room is still the best). Staff are a bit rude and arrogant, but it fits the vibe.
Pretty good coffee, fast wifi.... And roosters and chicks and cats and dogs all wandering around outside.
The bone marrow is insanely delicious. Have it with a stout.
According to my friend, who lived in Vietnam, this is the most authentic Vietnamese cuisine in all of Bali. And damn is it delicious. And damn is it spicy.
It's got a damn cool vibe, and the drinks are on point. Creative too. Best bar in the city? No. But excellent nonetheless.
Bitcoin accepted! Go for the Bullet Proof Coffee if you want something delicious & energizing. And you know how you never get enough bacon with breakfast? They give you enough. It's glorious.
The closest thing to America in Singapore, down to the fat guy in the backwards baseball cap. The damn batter-smothered onion rings are amazing. Go for the seats in the back, near the brewery.
The OMG burger is a delicious mess, the apple crumble is damn delectable, the music is quite good, and the ambiance is artsy and relaxed.
Really intriguing ambiance, some delicious items on the menu (the prawns in hot oil are delectable). Cool chef too.
The owner is a travelling photographer with amazing story-esque shots all along the walls & an attached gallery. Espresso is quite good too.
Considering we're in Bali, this is a pretty good barbershop. Their fade is a bit too strong, and they're no expert at balancing head hair & facial hair, but overall they know what they're doing.
A gigantic abandoned tropical theme park. Need I say more?
Really cool and relaxed place, kinda artsy, nice view of the rice fields. The green chai latte is good.

tip.text: Excellent hidden barber shop in the back, and the whole place has a badass hipster feel.
The pho is overrated. Not bad, but not as excellent as it's rumoured to be. Good wifi, cool proprietor.
Ducked into this place to escape the rain. Wound up eating the best Mac and Cheese we've ever had. Service is excellent, the vibe is cool. Overpriced with small portions..but excellently made.
The best burger I've ever had in my life. That home style burger tastes so damn good after two years abroad. I missed your sloppy perfection, Golden Star.
Delicious burgers for the cost, and not a bad vibe at all.
